with zero bias may not be practically feasible. Thus, instead of hoping for a model with zero bias in all the relevant
climatic parameters, we should make efforts to reduce the bias to the maximum extent possible. Seasonal mean
T2m and precipitation are the most important parameters that are required in several impact assessment studies
and hence have been used in this study.
The model tuning through manual methods is exhaustive and time-consuming. Yet, it provides better model con-
figuration for simulation of regional climate. The results from this study show that increase in horizontal resolution
alone will not improve the simulation effectively unless the model is simultaneously tuned. On the other hand, not
much can be achieved simply by manually tuning the model. We show that automatic parameter tuning is not that
effective, specifically in the context of Indian summer monsoon simulations. Therefore, it is suggested that both manual
